<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcb08594f-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s15902"><num value="15902">§ 15902.</num><heading> Enforcement by the Board</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Board may bring a civil action to enforce an order of the Board, except a civil action to enforce an order for the payment of money, when it is violated by a pipeline carrier providing transportation subject to this part.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idcb085950-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/104/88/tI/s106/a">Pub. L. 104–88, title I, § 106(a)</ref>, <date date="1995-12-29">Dec. 29, 1995</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/109/927">109 Stat. 927</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
